  Aerial photo taken on Oct. 28, 2021 shows the construction site of the Longmen Bridge in Qinzhou City, south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region. Located in the city of Qinzhou, the Longmen Bridge, a cross-sea bridge serving as a part of an expressway connecting coastal cities along the Beibu Gulf of Guangxi, stretches 7.6 km, with the main bridge body measuring 1,098 meters in length. (Xinhua/Zhou Hua)  